      <div xml:id="NA352-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu poruḷvayiṉ pirinta talaimakaṉ iṭaiccurattukkaṇ āṟṟāṉāyt taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE who had separated for the sake of wealth said to his own heart, being unable to bear it in the middle of the desert.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA352">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>          ilaimāṇ pakaḻic cilaimā ṇirīiya</l>
<l>          vaṉpi lāṭava ralaittaliṟ palaruṭaṉ</l>
<l>          vampalar tolainta varuñcurak kavalai</l>
<l>          yaḻalpōl ceviya cēva lāṭṭi</l>
<l>          niḻaloṭu katikku niṇampuri mutunari</l>
<l>          paccūṉ koḷḷai māntivey tuṟṟut</l>
<l>          tērtikaḻ vaṟumpulan tuḻaiiya nīrnayantu</l>
<l>          patukkai nīḻa lotukkiṭam peṟāa</l>
<l>          vañcuvaru kavalai varutaliṉ varuntiya</l>
<l>          namakku mariya vāyiṉa vamaittōṇ</l>
<l>          māṇpuṭaik kuṟumaka ṇīṅki</l>
<l>          yāṅkuvan taṉaḷko laḷiya ṭāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The crossroads of the difficult desert where travellers are lost,</l>
<l rend="indent">many together, to the beating of the loveless men</l>
<l rend="indent2">          that put into the glory of [their] bows arrows glorious for [their] blade,</l>
<l>        they have become difficult for us</l>
<l rend="indent2">          who suffered in coming along the fearful crossroads,</l>
<l rend="indent">          obtaining<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">peṟāa</term>: or "obtaning not [even] a single shady place..."</note> an isolate place of shade by the stone heap,</l>
<l rend="indent">          longing for the water stirred up on the poor field glittering with a mirage,<note place="foot">Here <term xml:lang="ta">tēr</term> probably only makes sense when read in the meaning of <term xml:lang="ta">veṇṭēr</term>.</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">          since he felt hot after having eaten the plunder of fresh flesh,</l>
<l rend="indent2">          by the old jackal<note place="foot">My suggestion for syntax is here to take <term xml:lang="ta">tuḻaiiya</term>, the less well attested variant and take this as a mark of subject change, i.e. taking <term xml:lang="ta">nari</term> as the subject of the preceding absolutives. If we read <term xml:lang="ta">uḻaii</term>, also absolutive, we will have to distribute arbitrarily between HIM and the jackal. One other possibility is still to read <term xml:lang="ta">peṟāa</term> simply as a negative <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> and as bearing a clause similar to the ones of the -<term xml:lang="ta">um</term> <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> ("the crossroad, where the jackal doesn’t obtain...").</note> desirous of fat, that moves with the shade<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">niḻaloṭu katikkum</term>: here T.V.G. understands the jackal to play with its shadow - but the context does not suggest that the jackal feels like playing.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">          chasing away the cock with ears like fire.</l>
<l rend="indent">          Having left the glorious little woman with bamboo shoulders,</l>
<l>        what has become of her, pitiable she?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
